From the Infowars web site :: On the July 22 edition of The Alex Jones Show, Alex will continue the discussion on the race war that's being promoted by our main stream media outlets. 

Alex talks with American film and television actor Ed Asner. 

Alex also interviews radio and television personality Larry Elder about his recent appearance on the Piers Morgan show where he defeated Piers in a debate about the true problems facing blacks in today's world. The Larry Elder Show airs weekdays on talk radio KABC in Los Angeles in which he supports free trade, school choice, same-sex marriage and abortion rights. Elder has authored several books and produced a DVD in which he attempts to repudiate filmmaker Michael Moore's anti-gun politics. 

Alex covers more details on the NSA spy scandal as new facts continue to emerge revealing how Obamacare is set to destroy the last of our privacy rights.
